@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">

    <h1 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-10">Last updated: April 7, 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-10 leading-relaxed">

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                Welcome to <strong>CodeWave</strong>. We are committed to protecting your personal information and
                your right to privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your
                information when you use our platform, including our web application, interactive coding
                environment, learning paths, quizzes, CV builder, and job board features.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3">
                By using CodeWave, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect the following types of information:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, password (hashed), and profile picture when you register.</li>
                <li><strong>OAuth Data:</strong> If you sign in via Google or GitHub, we receive your public profile information (name, email, avatar) from those providers.</li>
                <li><strong>Learning Activity:</strong> Completed lessons, exercise submissions, quiz attempts, assessment results, and study time.</li>
                <li><strong>CV &amp; Career Data:</strong> Information you voluntarily provide in the CV builder (education, experience, skills, certifications, projects).</li>
                <li><strong>Job Applications:</strong> Jobs you apply for and any cover letters submitted through the platform.</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, features used, browser type, and device information for improving the platform.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-2">
                <li>Create and manage your account and personalize your learning experience.</li>
                <li>Track your progress and recommend courses or lessons based on your skill level.</li>
                <li>Generate your CV and match your skills to job listings on the platform.</li>
                <li>Send you notifications about your learning progress via real-time updates.</li>
                <li>Improve and maintain the platform by analyzing usage patterns.</li>
                <li>Respond to your support requests and inquiries.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">4. Data Storage &amp; Security</h2>
            <p>
                Your data is stored in a secure SQL Server database hosted locally. We use industry-standard
                measures including:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-2">
                <li>Password hashing using ASP.NET Core Identity (bcrypt-based).</li>
                <li>HTTPS encryption for all data in transit.</li>
                <li>Session tokens stored in HttpOnly, Secure cookies with a 30-minute timeout.</li>
                <li>Soft-delete patterns — deleted records are flagged, not immediately removed, and permanently purged after 90 days.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">5. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>CodeWave integrates with the following third-party services:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Google OAuth &amp; GitHub OAuth:</strong> Used for social sign-in. Subject to Google's and GitHub's own privacy policies.</li>
                <li><strong>Google Gemini AI:</strong> Used to power the AI Helper feature in lessons. Only your question text is sent; no personal data is included.</li>
                <li><strong>Google Fonts:</strong> Used to load fonts. Subject to Google's privacy policy.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you.</li>
                <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate or incomplete data via your account settings.</li>
                <li><strong>Delete</strong> your account and associated data by contacting us.</li>
                <li><strong>Export</strong> your CV data in PDF format using the CV Builder feature.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">7. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>
                We retain your account data for as long as your account is active. Soft-deleted records
                (such as deleted courses or submissions) are permanently purged after 90 days. Temporary
                files generated during code execution are removed after 7 days.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page
                with an updated revision date. Continued use of CodeWave after changes are posted
                constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">9. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
                If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please
                contact us through the CodeWave platform or reach out to the administrator via the
                Admin Dashboard.
            </p>
        </section>

    </div>
</div>
